{
  "stem": "9168.7",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Then in 1979, President Carter established, by executive order, days of remembrance of victims of the Holocaust for April 28 and 29 1979 at-- in commemoration of-- asking the people of the United States quote, 'to observe this solemn anniversary in commemoration of the liberation of Dachau by US armed forces in-- on April 28, 29 1945.' That was--.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And from that time forward, I really felt that something was going to really start occurring as far as education on the Holocaust that had not been going on, other than in the Jewish World.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I could never understand why.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was in 19-- [LAUGHS] when I left Nuremberg and went back to Detroit, I had nightmares for three years.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was always escaping in a tunnel with little children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It must have been tunnels under the barbed wire fences at the camp with the Nazi guards walking back and forth with their bayoneted weapons and trying to keep little children from crying or making any noise in this escape with other people.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the same recurring nightmare for three years.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Nothing different, ever.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So in 1978 while I was in Congress, when the miniseries came on television four nights, there were four congressman, two Jewish and two non-Jewish, who asked me to watch it because they wanted to discuss it with me, knowing I had been at Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I watched that first night with the firebombing of the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I had the same recurring nightmare, which was 30 years later.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I could not-- I told them I couldn't watch the other three nights.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Now, today, I can watch anything, of course.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I was really very surprised that 30 years later I could not.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I came-- I came home by my terms.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
